verbose_text: In addition, the response of macrophages to NA does not only depend on the concentration of NA or the age of the animals, but also on the end products of their catabolism, such as HMPG (4-hydroxy-3-methoxyphenyl-glycol), which can establish a very fine tuned physiological regulation of macrophage functions, maintaining the phagocytic functions at physiologically optimal levels [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR - XREF_BIBR].
